    "tactics": "Young dragons open with Frightful Presence to scatter weaker foes, then unleash Fire Breath on clustered enemies. They use flight to stay mobile, strafing with breath weapon when recharged. In melee, they use Multiattack to focus down dangerous spellcasters. Dragons retreat if reduced below 60 HP, remembering enemies for future vengeance.",
    "attacksNotes": "<ul>\n<li><strong>Bite [Combat]:</strong> Melee attack (Agi 4 + Melee Combat 6), Reach: 10 ft\n<ul>\n<li><strong><em>Margin 1:</strong></em> 12 damage + 6 fire damage</li>\n<li><strong><em>Margin 2:</strong></em> 18 damage (12 + 6 Str) + 6 fire damage</li>\n</ul>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Claw [Combat]:</strong> Melee attack (Agi 4 + Melee Combat 6 vs opponent's defense), Reach: 5 ft\n<ul>\n<li><strong><em>Margin 1:</strong></em> 8 damage (Large, light weapon: 6 + 2)</li>\n<li><strong><em>Margin 2:</strong></em> 14 damage (8 + 6 Str)</li>\n</ul></li>\n</ul></li>\n<li><strong>Multiattack [Combat]:</strong> The dragon makes one bite attack and two claw attacks\n<ul>\n<li><strong><em>Shared Attribute Roll (Agi 4):</strong></em> Roll once, apply to all three attacks</li>\n</ul></li>\n</ul>",
    "specialAbilitiesNotes": "<ul>\n<li><strong>Large Size:</strong> Occupies 10×10 ft space, reach varies by attack\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Frightful Presence (3/day):</strong> Each creature of dragon's choice within 60 feet that can see it must make Will save (1 success needed):\n<ul>\n<li>Failure: Frightened for 1 minute (can repeat save at end of each turn)</li>\n<li>Success: Immune to this dragon's Frightful Presence for 24 hours</li>\n</ul></li>\n<li><strong>Dragon Senses:</strong> Darkvision 120 ft, Blindsight 30 ft</li>\n</ul></li>\n</ul>",
